revisions.description: The Port Access Entity module for managing AT Port Authentication.

AtrPaeControlledDirections.name: AtrPaeControlledDirections
AtrPaeControlledDirections.description: The control mode values for the Authenticator PAE.

AtrPaeControlledPortStatus.name: AtrPaeControlledPortStatus
AtrPaeControlledPortStatus.description: The status values of the Authenticator PAE controlled Port.

AtrPaeControlledPortControl.name: AtrPaeControlledPortControl
AtrPaeControlledPortControl.description: The control values of the Authenticator PAE controlled Port.

atrDot1xPaePortTable.name: atrDot1xPaePortTable
atrDot1xPaePortTable.description: A table of system level information for each port supported by the Port Access Entity. An entry appears in this table for each port of this system.

atrDot1xPaePortEntry.name: atrDot1xPaePortEntry
atrDot1xPaePortEntry.description: The Port number, protocol version, and initialisation control for a Port.

atrDot1xPaePortNumber.name: atrDot1xPaePortNumber
atrDot1xPaePortNumber.description: The Port number associated with this Port.

atrDot1xPaePortProtocolVersion.name: atrDot1xPaePortProtocolVersion
atrDot1xPaePortProtocolVersion.description: The protocol version associated with this Port.

atrDot1xPaePortCapabilities.name: atrDot1xPaePortCapabilities
atrDot1xPaePortCapabilities.description: Indicates the PAE functionality that this Port supports and that may be managed through this MIB.

atrDot1xPaePortInitialise.name: atrDot1xPaePortInitialise
atrDot1xPaePortInitialise.description: The initialisation control for this Port. Setting this attribute TRUE causes the Port to be initialised. The attribute value reverts to FALSE once initialisation has completed.

atrDot1xPaePortReauthenticate.name: atrDot1xPaePortReauthenticate
atrDot1xPaePortReauthenticate.description: The reauthentication control for this port. Setting this attribute TRUE causes the Authenticator PAE state machine for the Port to reauthenticate the Supplicant. Setting this attribute FALSE has no effect. This attribute always returns FALSE when it is read.

atrDot1xPaePortSuppMacAddress.name: atrDot1xPaePortSuppMacAddress
atrDot1xPaePortSuppMacAddress.description: The six character MAC Address of the attached supplicant.

atrDot1xAuthConfigTable.name: atrDot1xAuthConfigTable
atrDot1xAuthConfigTable.description: A table that contains the configuration objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each port. An entry appears in this table for each port that may authenticate access to itself.

atrDot1xAuthConfigEntry.name: atrDot1xAuthConfigEntry
atrDot1xAuthConfigEntry.description: The configuration information for an Authenticator PAE.

atrDot1xAuthPaeState.name: atrDot1xAuthPaeState
atrDot1xAuthPaeState.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine.

atrDot1xAuthBackendAuthState.name: atrDot1xAuthBackendAuthState
atrDot1xAuthBackendAuthState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

atrDot1xAuthAdminControlledDirections.name: atrDot1xAuthAdminControlledDirections
atrDot1xAuthAdminControlledDirections.description: The current value of the administrative controlled directions parameter for the Port.

atrDot1xAuthOperControlledDirections.name: atrDot1xAuthOperControlledDirections
atrDot1xAuthOperControlledDirections.description: The current value of the operational controlled directions parameter for the Port.

atrDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortStatus.name: atrDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortStatus
atrDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortStatus.description: The current value of the controlled Port status parameter for the Port.

atrDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl.name: atrDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl
atrDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl.description: The current value of the controlled Port control parameter for the Port.

atrDot1xAuthQuietPeriod.name: atrDot1xAuthQuietPeriod
atrDot1xAuthQuietPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the quietPeriod constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

atrDot1xAuthTxPeriod.name: atrDot1xAuthTxPeriod
atrDot1xAuthTxPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the txPeriod constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

atrDot1xAuthSuppTimeout.name: atrDot1xAuthSuppTimeout
atrDot1xAuthSuppTimeout.description: The value, in seconds, of the suppTimeout constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

atrDot1xAuthServerTimeout.name: atrDot1xAuthServerTimeout
atrDot1xAuthServerTimeout.description: The value, in seconds, of the serverTimeout constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

atrDot1xAuthMaxReq.name: atrDot1xAuthMaxReq
atrDot1xAuthMaxReq.description: The value of the maxReq constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

atrDot1xAuthReAuthPeriod.name: atrDot1xAuthReAuthPeriod
atrDot1xAuthReAuthPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the reAuthPeriod constant currently in use by the Reauthentication Timer state machine.

atrDot1xAuthReAuthEnabled.name: atrDot1xAuthReAuthEnabled
atrDot1xAuthReAuthEnabled.description: The enable/disable control used by the Reauthentication Timer state machine (8.5.5.1).

atrDot1xAuthKeyTxEnabled.name: atrDot1xAuthKeyTxEnabled
atrDot1xAuthKeyTxEnabled.description: The value of the keyTransmissionEnabled constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

atrDot1xAuthPreAuthVlan.name: atrDot1xAuthPreAuthVlan
atrDot1xAuthPreAuthVlan.description: The VLAN name of the VLAN that this port belonged to prior to RADIUS authentication.

atrDot1xAuthPostAuthVlan.name: atrDot1xAuthPostAuthVlan
atrDot1xAuthPostAuthVlan.description: The VLAN name of the VLAN that this port belongs to since RADIUS authentication.

atrDot1xAuthLastAuthReason.name: atrDot1xAuthLastAuthReason
atrDot1xAuthLastAuthReason.description: Should the supplicant have failed authentication, this records the reason for the last failure. Never is returned in the case the supplicant has never failed.

atrDot1XAuthVlanAssignment.name: atrDot1XAuthVlanAssignment
atrDot1XAuthVlanAssignment.description: Specifies whether VLAN Assignment is to be performed on the port. When set to TRUE, the VLAN Assignment mechanism will run, when set to FALSE it will not.

atrDot1XAuthSecureVlan.name: atrDot1XAuthSecureVlan
atrDot1XAuthSecureVlan.description: Only valid in Multi-Supplicant mode, this parameter defines whether to allow supplicants to authenticate on a port, when there is already an authenticated aupplicant on the port

atrDot1xAuthGuestVlan.name: atrDot1xAuthGuestVlan
atrDot1xAuthGuestVlan.description: This value defines a temporary VLAN to assign to a port while there is no 802.1X host connected to it.

atrDot1XAuthMibReset.name: atrDot1XAuthMibReset
atrDot1XAuthMibReset.description: Only valid in Multi-Supplicant mode, this parameter defines whether to age out MIB information stored for old supplicants.

atrDot1xAuthTrap.name: atrDot1xAuthTrap
atrDot1xAuthTrap.description: Specifies what events trigger an SNMP trap.

atrDot1xAuthStatsTable.name: atrDot1xAuthStatsTable
atrDot1xAuthStatsTable.description: A table that contains the statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each Port. An entry appears in this table for each port that may authenticate access to itself.

atrDot1xAuthStatsEntry.name: atrDot1xAuthStatsEntry
atrDot1xAuthStatsEntry.description: The statistics information for an Authenticator PAE.

atrDot1xAuthEapolFramesRx.name: atrDot1xAuthEapolFramesRx
atrDot1xAuthEapolFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAPOL frames of any type that have been received by this Authenticator.

atrDot1xAuthEapolFramesTx.name: atrDot1xAuthEapolFramesTx
atrDot1xAuthEapolFramesTx.description: The number of EAPOL frames of any type that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

atrDot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx.name: atrDot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx
atrDot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Start frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

atrDot1xAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.name: atrDot1xAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx
atrDot1xAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Logoff frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

atrDot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.name: atrDot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx
atrDot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.description: The number of EAP Resp/Id frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

atrDot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx.name: atrDot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx
atrDot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAP Response frames (other than Resp/Id frames) that have been received by this Authenticator.

atrDot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.name: atrDot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx
atrDot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Req/Id frames that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

atrDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx.name: atrDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx
atrDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Request frames (other than Rq/Id frames) that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

atrDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.name: atrDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx
atrDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the frame type is not recognised.

atrDot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.name: atrDot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx
atrDot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the Packet Body Length field is invalid.

atrDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.name: atrDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion
atrDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.description: The protocol version number carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

atrDot1xAuthenticated.name: atrDot1xAuthenticated
atrDot1xAuthenticated.description: Triggered when a supplicant is authenticated on a port.

atrDot1xUnauthenticated.name: atrDot1xUnauthenticated
atrDot1xUnauthenticated.description: Triggered when a supplicant who was previously authorised on a port, is no longer authorised. This can be due to an authentication timeout, log off or disconnection of the port.

atrDot1xFailedAuth.name: atrDot1xFailedAuth
atrDot1xFailedAuth.description: Triggered when a supplicant is unable to be authorised on a port.

atrMacBasedAuthPaePortTable.name: atrMacBasedAuthPaePortTable
atrMacBasedAuthPaePortTable.description: A table of system level information for each port supported by the Port Access Entity. An entry appears in this table for each port of this system.

atrMacBasedAuthPaePortEntry.name: atrMacBasedAuthPaePortEntry
atrMacBasedAuthPaePortEntry.description: The Port number, protocol version, and initialisation control for a Port.

atrMacBasedAuthPaePortNumber.name: atrMacBasedAuthPaePortNumber
atrMacBasedAuthPaePortNumber.description: The Port number associated with this Port.

atrMacBasedAuthPaePortInitialise.name: atrMacBasedAuthPaePortInitialise
atrMacBasedAuthPaePortInitialise.description: The initialisation control for this Port. Setting this attribute TRUE causes the Port to be initialised. The attribute value reverts to FALSE once initialisation has completed.

atrMacBasedAuthPaePortReauthenticate.name: atrMacBasedAuthPaePortReauthenticate
atrMacBasedAuthPaePortReauthenticate.description: The reauthentication control for this port. Setting this attribute TRUE causes the Authenticator PAE state machine for the Port to reauthenticate the Supplicant. Setting this attribute FALSE has no effect. This attribute always returns FALSE when it is read.

atrMacBasedAuthPaePortSuppMacAddress.name: atrMacBasedAuthPaePortSuppMacAddress
atrMacBasedAuthPaePortSuppMacAddress.description: The six character MAC Address of the attached supplicant.

atrMacBasedAuthConfigTable.name: atrMacBasedAuthConfigTable
atrMacBasedAuthConfigTable.description: A table that contains the configuration objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each port. An entry appears in this table for each port that may authenticate access to itself.

atrMacBasedAuthConfigEntry.name: atrMacBasedAuthConfigEntry
atrMacBasedAuthConfigEntry.description: The configuration information for an Authenticator PAE.

atrMacBasedAuthPaeState.name: atrMacBasedAuthPaeState
atrMacBasedAuthPaeState.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine.

atrMacBasedAuthBackendAuthState.name: atrMacBasedAuthBackendAuthState
atrMacBasedAuthBackendAuthState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

atrMacBasedAuthControlledPortStatus.name: atrMacBasedAuthControlledPortStatus
atrMacBasedAuthControlledPortStatus.description: The current value of the controlled Port status parameter for the Port.

atrMacBasedAuthControlledPortControl.name: atrMacBasedAuthControlledPortControl
atrMacBasedAuthControlledPortControl.description: The current value of the controlled Port control parameter for the Port.

atrMacBasedAuthQuietPeriod.name: atrMacBasedAuthQuietPeriod
atrMacBasedAuthQuietPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the quietPeriod constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

atrMacBasedAuthReAuthPeriod.name: atrMacBasedAuthReAuthPeriod
atrMacBasedAuthReAuthPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the reAuthPeriod constant currently in use by the Reauthentication Timer state machine.

atrMacBasedAuthReAuthEnabled.name: atrMacBasedAuthReAuthEnabled
atrMacBasedAuthReAuthEnabled.description: The enable/disable control used by the Reauthentication Timer state machine.

atrMacBasedAuthPreAuthVlan.name: atrMacBasedAuthPreAuthVlan
atrMacBasedAuthPreAuthVlan.description: The VLAN name of the VLAN that this port belonged to prior to RADIUS authentication.

atrMacBasedAuthPostAuthVlan.name: atrMacBasedAuthPostAuthVlan
atrMacBasedAuthPostAuthVlan.description: The VLAN name of the VLAN that this port belongs to since RADIUS authentication.

atrMacBasedAuthLastAuthReason.name: atrMacBasedAuthLastAuthReason
atrMacBasedAuthLastAuthReason.description: Should the supplicant have failed authentication, this records the reason for the last failure. Never is returned in the case the supplicant has never failed.

atrMacBasedAuthVlanAssignment.name: atrMacBasedAuthVlanAssignment
atrMacBasedAuthVlanAssignment.description: Specifies whether VLAN Assignment is to be performed on the port. When set to TRUE, the VLAN Assignment mechanism will run, when set to FALSE it will not.

atrMacBasedAuthSecureVlan.name: atrMacBasedAuthSecureVlan
atrMacBasedAuthSecureVlan.description: Only valid in Multi-Supplicant mode, this parameter defines whether to allow supplicants to authenticate on a port, when there is already an authenticated aupplicant on the port

atrMacBasedAuthMibReset.name: atrMacBasedAuthMibReset
atrMacBasedAuthMibReset.description: Only valid in Multi-Supplicant mode, this parameter defines whether to age out MIB information stored for old supplicants.

atrMacBasedAuthTrap.name: atrMacBasedAuthTrap
atrMacBasedAuthTrap.description: Specifies what events trigger an SNMP trap.

atrMacBasedAuthAuthenticated.name: atrMacBasedAuthAuthenticated
atrMacBasedAuthAuthenticated.description: Triggered when a supplicant is authenticated on a port.

atrMacBasedAuthUnauthenticated.name: atrMacBasedAuthUnauthenticated
atrMacBasedAuthUnauthenticated.description: Triggered when a supplicant who was previously authorised on a port, is no longer authorised. This can be due to a authentication timeout or a failed reauthentication.

atrMacBasedAuthFailedAuth.name: atrMacBasedAuthFailedAuth
atrMacBasedAuthFailedAuth.description: Triggered when a supplicant is unable to be authorised on a port.
